{"h3":"Five parties agree Rotterdam coalition with one-seat majority","summary":"PRO, VVD, D66, Volt and CDA struck a deal to govern Rotterdam, securing a wafer-thin one-seat majority on the council.","body":["After weeks of talks the five parties reached agreement on a programme for Rotterdam, the country's second city, ending uncertainty over who would run the local administration. The coalition holds just a single seat majority, which observers say could make the council vulnerable to wobbles.","The deal mirrors the centrist alliances forming in other big cities as the radical right struggles to translate national gains into local power. Housing construction and public safety are expected to top the new board's agenda."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/five-parties-agree-coalition-in-rotterdam-with-one-seat-majority/")]},
