{"h3":"FVD councillor spent thousands in tax money on steak dinners","summary":"A Forum voor Democratie councillor charged thousands of euros of public money on expensive steak dinners, drawing accusations of misusing taxpayer funds.","body":["An investigation found the FVD politician had run up large bills on lavish meals that were charged to the public purse. The revelation has prompted calls for repayment and a review of expense rules.","The case adds to a run of embarrassing headlines for the radical right party and feeds a wider debate about transparency in local government spending. Opponents seized on the story to question the party's claims to represent ordinary voters."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/fvd-councillor-spent-thousands-in-tax-money-on-steak-dinners/")]},
{"h3":"Employers unhappy with Jetten cabinet performance so far","summary":"Dutch employers organisations voiced frustration with the new cabinet, saying it has been too slow to act on business priorities.","body":["Business lobby groups said the Jetten government had yet to deliver on key issues such as labour market reform, energy costs and investment, leaving employers disappointed after the first months in office. The criticism echoes polls showing public patience with the cabinet wearing thin.","The minority government's reliance on shifting parliamentary support has slowed decision making, employers argue. The cabinet says it is working through a heavy agenda and that meaningful reform takes time."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/employers-not-happy-with-dutch-cabinet-performance-so-far/")]},
{"sub":"Economy & Housing","h3":"Dutch house prices hit new record with 4.4% annual increase","summary":"Average house prices reached a fresh record high in May, up 4.4% on the year, as the chronic housing shortage kept the market hot.","body":["Figures show prices climbing again to an all time high, though the pace of growth has eased sharply from the near double digit jumps of a year ago. Persistent undersupply continues to push buyers to bid above asking price.","Economists expect prices to keep rising through 2026 at a more moderate 4 to 5 percent. The squeeze remains toughest for first time buyers, many of whom are priced out of the big cities."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/dutch-house-prices-hit-new-record-with-4-4-annual-increase/")]},
{"h3":"New private renters now spend 35% of income on housing","summary":"First time private tenants hand over more than a third of their income on rent, statistics agency CBS reported.","body":["CBS found that people entering the private rental market for the first time spend on average around 35 percent of their income on housing, a level widely seen as unaffordable. The figure underscores how the rental crisis is hitting newcomers and young people hardest.","The data lands as a separate study from budget institute Nibud showed most young adults now struggle to make ends meet. Together the reports paint a bleak picture of affordability for those at the start of their working lives."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/first-time-private-renters-spend-most-of-income-on-housing-cbs/"),("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/most-young-adults-now-struggle-to-make-ends-meet-nibud-finds/")]},
{"h3":"Plans for 30,000 homes stall over missing roads and rail money","summary":"Construction of tens of thousands of planned homes is blocked because funding for supporting roads and railways has not been secured.","body":["Projects that would deliver some 30,000 new homes are on hold because the infrastructure needed to connect them, from access roads to rail links, lacks financing. The bottleneck highlights how the housing shortage is tangled up with wider spending shortfalls.","Developers and councils are pressing the cabinet to release the money, warning that delays will deepen the supply crisis. The government faces hard choices over how to fund the roads and rail that new neighbourhoods depend on."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/plans-for-30000-homes-stall-over-missing-roads-and-rail-money/")]},
{"h3":"Heineken names JDE Peet's executive Rafa Oliveira as new CEO","summary":"Brewing giant Heineken appointed Brazilian executive Rafael Oliveira as chief executive, handing him a share package worth 25 million euros.","body":["Heineken's board tapped Oliveira, currently at coffee group JDE Peet's, to take the top job at one of the country's best known multinationals. He will receive a share award reported at around 25 million euros as part of his pay deal.","The appointment marks a generational shift at the Amsterdam listed brewer as it navigates softer demand and rising costs. Investors will watch how the incoming chief executive balances growth with shareholder returns."],"sources":[("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/heineken-board-taps-jde-peets-exec-rafa-oliveira-new-ceo"),("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/incoming-heineken-chief-receives-25-million-euro-share-package")]},
{"h3":"NS cancels trains on key routes as extreme heat hits","summary":"Rail operator NS scrapped services on several main lines because of the heatwave and told travellers to carry water.","body":["With temperatures forecast to climb towards record June highs, NS announced cancellations on key routes to protect overheating track and equipment. The operator urged passengers to bring water and plan journeys carefully.","The disruption comes on top of the planned transport strike, compounding misery for commuters. Schools cut hours and the RIVM issued heat and smog warnings as the country braced for its hottest days of the year."],"sources":[("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/ns-cancelling-trains-key-routes-week-due-heat-passengers-will-need-water"),("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/schools-cut-hours-as-knmi-issues-extreme-heat-warning/")]},
{"sub":"Society & Culture","h3":"Netherlands confirms first euthanasia of a child under 12","summary":"A terminally ill child under the age of 12 has died through euthanasia for the first time since the law was widened two years ago.","body":["Health minister Sophie Hermans confirmed that the case, which took place late last year, was reported to the committee that reviews assisted deaths of children. It is the first such death since the rules were extended to cover younger children.","The disclosure reopens a sensitive ethical debate about end of life decisions for the very young. Officials stressed that the strict safeguards built into the law had been followed in full."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/netherlands-records-first-euthanasia-death-of-child-under-12/"),("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/first-euthanasia-terminally-ill-child-confirmed-netherlands")]},
{"h3":"Acclaimed Dutch poet and philosopher Lieke Marsman dies aged 35","summary":"Award winning writer and former Poet Laureate Lieke Marsman has died at the age of 35 after living with cancer for years.","body":["Marsman, who served as the national Poet Laureate and was admired for blending poetry with philosophy and political reflection, died at 35. She had written openly about her illness throughout her career.","Tributes poured in from across the literary world for a voice seen as one of the most original of her generation. Her work spanned poetry, essays and translation and reached a wide readership."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/acclaimed-dutch-poet-and-philosopher-lieke-marsman-dies-aged-35/")]},
{"h3":"At least 41 wolves likely poached in the Netherlands since 2021","summary":"A new study estimates one in seven Dutch wolves has been illegally killed by poachers since the animals returned in 2021.","body":["Researchers concluded that at least 41 wolves have probably been shot or otherwise killed illegally since the protected species re established itself in the country. The findings point to persistent conflict between wolves and rural communities.","The return of the wolf has divided opinion, with farmers worried about livestock and conservationists defending the animal's protected status. Authorities face pressure to crack down on poaching while easing tensions in affected areas."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/one-in-seven-dutch-wolves-illegally-killed-by-poachers-study/"),("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/report-says-least-41-wolves-likely-poached-netherlands-since-2021")]},
{"h3":"Mauritshuis can keep disputed Rembrandts, court rules","summary":"A court ruled the Mauritshuis museum in The Hague may keep two Rembrandt paintings claimed by the heirs of a former donor.","body":["The dispute centred on whether the descendants of an original benefactor could reclaim the works from the museum's collection. Judges sided with the Mauritshuis, allowing the celebrated paintings to stay on public display.","The ruling brings relief to one of the country's leading art institutions and settles a long running ownership question. The Rembrandts remain among the highlights of the museum's Golden Age holdings."],"sources":[("DutchNews","https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/06/mauritshuis-can-keep-rembrandts-in-dispute-with-donors-heirs/")]},
{"h3":"Life sentence sought for Dutch-Rwandan man over 1994 genocide","summary":"Prosecutors demanded a life sentence for a Dutch-Rwandan man accused of involvement in the massacre of around 3,000 Tutsi during the 1994 genocide.","body":["The man stands trial in the Netherlands over allegations he played a role in the killing of some 3,000 Tutsi who had sought refuge during the Rwandan genocide. Prosecutors called for the maximum penalty of life imprisonment.","The case is one of several brought under Dutch universal jurisdiction rules that allow the country to try grave international crimes. A verdict is expected later this year."],"sources":[("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/06/23/life-sentence-sought-dutch-rwandan-man-massacre-3000-tutsi-1994-genocide")]}
